    "created_at": "2015-09-06T08:44:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-06T08:44:31Z",
    "body": "> We have Windows CI running on GitHub's own server, but it does not test pushes by non-GitHubbers for security reasons, so for now I can only verify Electron builds on Windows when I push.\n\nIs it possible to configure the internal CI to also run on merge?\nThat way code that was pushed by a non GitHubber, will still go through some form of automatic testing on Windows.\n"
